<H3> <TI>   Fuzzy Control in Gas and Oil Geophysics Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fuzzy Control in Gas and Oil Geophysics Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   947G0006D Moscow TEKHNICHESKAYA KIBERNETIKA in Russian No. 
5, Sep 93-Oct 93 (manuscript received 31 Mar 93) pp 141-148 </F>

<F P=103> 947G0006D </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow TEKHNICHESKAYA KIBERNETIKA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Ya. I. Khurgin, Moscow; UDC 51.57.591] </F>
  [Abstract] The inadequacy of the probabilistic-statistical 
approach to data processing is shown in a geophysical study of 
wells. The drawbacks of this approach are discussed in detail. 
The proposed alternative is the treatment of measured parameters 
as fuzzy numbers and the determination of the main parameters of 
oil- and gas-bearing strata (obtained by solving petrophysical 
equations) as solutions of fuzzy systems of algebraic equations. 
The appropriate mathematical vehicle is developed. The problem 
of solving a fuzzy linear system of algebraic equations is 
reduced to a nonlinear programming problem. Figure 1; referenc 
es 10: 5 Russian, 5 Western. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

