<H3> <TI>   Correctness of Parallel Microprograms with Different </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Correctness of Parallel Microprograms with Different </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Microinstruction   Execution Times 

<F P=102> 947G0009 Moscow PROGRAMMIROVANIYE in Russian No. 5, Sep 
93-Oct 93 (manuscript received 6 Feb 92; after revision 19 Mar </F>

93)pp 74-85 
<F P=103> 947G0009 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PROGRAMMIROVANIYE </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by S. M. Achasova, Computing Center of the </F>
Siberian Division of the Russian Academy of Sciences; UDC 
681.322] 
  [Abstract] Synchronized interpretation of parallel 
microprograms with different microinstruction execution times 
over cellular arr ays is studied. A description of asynchronous 
implementation of parallel microinstructions and the definition 
of its correctnes s is contrasted with a model of synchronized 
interpretation. A number of examples are presented. A method of 
resolving the situation of possible command conflict is 
outlined. The necessary and sufficient conditions for the 
correctness of the interpretation are formulated and a method is 
presented to recognize incorrect interpretation using the text 
of the microprogram. Figures 11; references 9: 8 Russian, 1 
Western. 

