<F P=103> 947G0012A </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev IZVESTIYA VYSSHIKH UCHEBNYKH ZAVEDENIY: 
RADIOELEKTRONIKA </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by A. I. Litvin; UDC 681.32.06] </F>
  [Abstract] The possibility is examined for using orthogonal 
Walsh and Fourier matrices for circular testing in linear 
discrete devices and in multiprocessor computer systems of the 
SIMD type. In order check that the logical and arithmetic 
operations are properly carried out, the task of mutual testing 
in a multiprocessor computer system with a distributed floating 
kernel is resolved. It was found that the use of orthogonal 
discrete Fourier and Walsh transforms made it simple and 
efficient to properly control the way logical and arithmetic 
operations are carried out in computers. 4 figures and 8 
references. 


