<H3> <TI>   Optimization of Nutrient Medium for Cultivating Yersinia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Optimization of Nutrient Medium for Cultivating Yersinia </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Pestis   Vacccine Strain Using Mathematical Experimental Design 

<F P=102> 947C0199A Kiev MIKROBIOLOGICHESKIY ZHURNAL in Russian Vol. 
54, No. 3, May-Jun 92 p 110--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 947C0199A </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev MIKROBIOLOGICHESKIY ZHURNAL </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Synopsis of article by N. V. Lopatina, A. N. Terentyev, L. </F>
A. Natalich and Sh. U. Yangulov, deposited at VINITI 3 Jan 92 
No. 1-V92; UDC 579.842.23:57.083.134.51]] 
  [Text] The PPE-2[.sup]4[/] mathematical experimental 
design method is used to optimize a nutrient medium for 
cultivating a vaccine strain of Yersinia pestis. The 
proposed medium contains splenic autolysate with the addition of 
wheat bran protein hydrolysate, 0.0005 percent of twin 80, 
0.0005 percent of twin 60, 0.0001 percent of thiourea and 0.001 
percent of Ca[.sup]2+[/]. 
  Cells of vaccine strain of Yersinia pestis that 
reproduce on this medium have high virulence and resistance to 
the lyophilization process. 

</TEXT>

